description: Number of rooted 2-dimensional polyominoes with n pentagonal cells, with no symmetries removed.
comments: Number of polypents (like polyominoes, with pentagons) with n cells. These are anchored polypents, with no culling for reflection or rotation (or translation) isomorphism.
references: Dan Hoey, Bill Gosper and Rich Schroeppel, Discussions in Math-Fun Mailing list, circa Jul 13 1999.
links: R. C. Schroeppel, A few mathematical experiments
author: Richard Schroeppel, Feb 13 2002
extensions: More terms from _N. J. A. Sloane_, May 06 2004
